    <div style="font-family: 'Arial Rounded MT Bold'; font-size: 20px;">
    <h2 style="font-family: 'Arial Black'">The Logic University Stationery Store Inventory System</h2>
    <h4 style="font-size: 18px">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; - an IT solution targeted at automating the stationery store’s operations.</h4>
    <br />
    <h3>The inventory system will be made accessible to Logic University Staff, and incorporates the following functions:</h3>
    <ul style="list-style-type: disc;">
        <li>Capture stock item information electronically; e.g. pricing details, reorder levels and reorder quantities</li>
        <li>Allow employee to request for stationery from their own PC at any time</li>
        <li>Inform department heads through email that there are outstanding requests awaiting their approval; they would also be able to approve these requests from their own PC at any time</li>
        <li>Allow department heads to delegate their authority to another employee during their absence from the office</li>
        <li>List current and previous stationery requisitions and its disbursement status upon employees’ requests</li>
        <li>Allow clerk to keep track of out-standing requisitions and fulfill the requisitions when the stock is replenished</li>
        <li>Allow clerk to keep track of stock levels and reporting on low stock levels</li>
        <li>Allow printing of stock items for tender and re-order</li>
        <li>Inform employees on status of requisition through email</li>
        <li>Maintain suppliers’ and departments’ information</li>
        <li>Allow printing of disbursement list for delivery trips</li>
        <li>Allow generation of reports to provide trend analysis of stock item movements</li>
    </ul>
